
extend layout

block content
  header#overview.jumbotron.subhead
    div.container
      h1 Getting started
      p.lead Let's get started on how to use teambition UI in a web app or a website.

  div.container
    div.row
      div.span3.bs-docs-sidebar
        ul.nav.nav-list.bs-docs-sidenav
          li
            a(href="#install-teambition-ui")
              | Install
          li
            a(href="#file-structure")
              | File structure
          li
            a(href="#usage")
              | Usage
          li
            a(href="#what-next")
              | What next?

      div.span9
        section#install-teambition-ui
          div.page-header
            h1 1. Install
          p.lead Using bower to install teambition UI kit is considered as the
            | best practice.
          pre.prettyprint.
            bower install git@github.com:Teambition/UI.git

        section#file-structure
          div.page-header
            h1 2. File Structure
          p.lead After installing teambition UI, you will get the following
            | file structure in your components directory:
          pre.prettyprint.
            UI/
            ├── docs/
            │   ├── where this document located
            ├── img/
            │   ├── images
            └── js/
            │   ├── javascript components - only for static site use
            └── less/
            │   ├── source code of styles
            └── several configuration files

        section#usage
          div.page-header
            h1 3. Usage
          p.lead Just include the compiled stylesheet to use:
          pre.prettyprint.
            link(href="pathToUI/assets/css/teambition-ui.css")
          p.lead
            | When writing a static site, you may want to use responsive
            | styles, simply include the following files:
          pre.prettyprint.
            link(href="pathToUI/assets/css/teambition-ui-responsive.css")
            script(src"pathToUI/assets/js/teambition-ui.js")
          p.lead If you want to add extra styles, make sure you include the
            | basic variables and mixins to keep your styles matching with the
            | UI kit:
          pre.prettyprint.
            // add these lines in the head of your less file
            @import "../components/UI/less/mixins";
            @import "../components/UI/less/variables";

        section#what-next
          div.page-header
            h1 4. What's next
          p.lead
            | Read the following parts of this document to get more
            | information and code snippets.
          a.btn.btn-large.btn-primary(href="./base-css.html")
            | Find out all base components now